SIMPLE: four-way
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Four-way
<hw>Four"-way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Allowing passage in
either of four directions; <as>as, a <ex>four-way</ex> cock, or
valve</as>.</def> <rj><au>Francis.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Four-way cock</b></col>, <cd>a cock connected with four
pipes or ports, and having two or more passages in the plug, by which
the adjacent pipes or ports may be made to communicate; formerly used as
a valve in the steam engine, and now for various other purposes. In the
illustration, <xex>a</xex> leads to the upper end of a steam engine
cylinder, and <xex>b</xex> to the lower end; <xex>c</xex> is the steam
pipe, and <xex>d</xex> the exhaust pipe.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Four-way stop</ent>⟦br⟧
